<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06039g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06039g">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06039g"> 39(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> chasse ferm&eacute;e (gate)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Cette tendance &agrave; tout animer porte l&apos;enfant &agrave; r&eacute;ifier ou &agrave; personnifier m&ecirc;me des abstractions. &hellip; ces mots: &ldquo;<mark>La chasse est ferm&eacute;e</mark>&rdquo;, &eacute;voquent dans l&apos;esprit de Paul, je le vois &agrave; ses questions, l&apos;id&eacute;e de <mark>grandes portes</mark> qui cl&ocirc;tureraient les champs. <font color="green">[This tendency to animate everything leads the child to reify or to personify even abstractions. &hellip; these words: &ldquo;The hunt is closed&rdquo;, evoke in Paul&apos;s mind, I see him to his questions, the idea of large doors that would fence the fields.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 12</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
